It's sickly sweet.
Your allowed to be naughty in this VR game.
It does teach you how to use one handed VR guns properly and prepare for future VR gun games.
1. Grab a gun that has no lazer sights.
2. Close your left eye.
3. Support your right hand with your left hand.
4. learn how to get the gun level by looking through the sights.
5. Shoot the moving pink men.
6. Rinse and repeat.

Too bad there was no one online when I tried, but I had fun while it lasted. There is just the one room with a few way to interact as listed in the description. As others have mentioned, movement is painful which ruins the experience. At least there are achievements that give you a sense of accomplishment when you do something!
Not a huge fan of these 'toy box' type games. It's more like a VR intro demo than a game. The movement also needs some work.

Movement controls are easily the worst I've experienced in VR, to the point that I'd doubt anyone even bothered playing it before release if it wasn't an otherwise polished experience. Snap turning requires pressing the thumbstick in, and moving around is accomplished by pressing the thumbstick forward, at which point you'll move about 6" forward in space in whichever direction you're facing, including altitude (so, if you're looking up, you go up. Looking down, you go down). Then, you have to repeat the thumbstick movement again to move another 6 inches. If you hold it forward, nothing happens. I gave back one star because I'm pretty sure this would be a nifty experience if not for the abominable movement.

The shooting mini game is actually quite nice, but the way you have to navigate through the room is painful. Everytime you want to move foward, you are also going down and find yourself almost underneath the table, where the guns are.
The shooting is actually very fun, as are the grabbing mechanics. But as others have pointed out, it's critically flawed. DEVS: PLEASE make the movement only affect horizontal, not vertical!
